                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[You Can Roll Dice in the Linux Terminal, Here's How]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/you-can-roll-dice-in-the-linux-terminal-heres-how/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ali Haider]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/set-of-red-dungeons-dragons-dice-on-a-character-sheet-next-to-a-figurine-and-book.jpg" length="353" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux & macOS Terminal]]></category><category><![CDATA[tabletop]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            No more hunting for dice under the sofa.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>We usually think of the terminal as something purely functional—tweaking Linux settings, installing updates, or running commands for work. And for most people, that’s where it ends. But the terminal can be more versatile than you might expect. One surprisingly fun use case? Rolling dice. Yes, your Linux terminal can double as a digital dice roller.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/you-can-roll-dice-in-the-linux-terminal-heres-how/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Switched to Home Assistant's New Dashboard, and It's Now My Favorite Hub]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-switched-to-home-assistants-new-dashboard-and-its-now-my-favorite-hub/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/the-experimental-home-dashboard-in-home-assistant-on-a-samsung-galaxy-z-fold-6.jpg" length="1017" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home Assistant]]></category><category><![CDATA[Matter]]></category><category><![CDATA[automation]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A dashboard that better assists your home. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I want to love Home Assistant, but it has felt overly complex compared to the likes of Samsung SmartThings and Google Home. Thankfully, there's a new dashboard on the way that completely rewrites my first impression.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 16:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-switched-to-home-assistants-new-dashboard-and-its-now-my-favorite-hub/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Hidden Setting Sped Up My Android Phone]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-hidden-setting-sped-up-my-android-phone/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/hand-holding-a-phone-with-the-android-mascot-holding-a-settings-gear-in-front-of-the-screen.png" length="1323" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's the first setting I change on every new phone.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>How fast your Android phone feels isn’t just about the hardware. Software optimizations and features like animations play a big role in responsiveness. Fortunately, there’s a simple animation trick that works on basically every Android device.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-hidden-setting-sped-up-my-android-phone/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Was Skeptical, But Now I'm Glad There's an App for Everything]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/i-was-skeptical-but-now-im-glad-theres-an-app-for-everything/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/smiling_woman_using_a_smartphone_with_colorful_app_icons_floating_beside_her.png" length="2178" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple App Store]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Hold on—let me pull out my phone for this. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>As a long-time smartphone skeptic, I resented their role in our lives. Now I’ve not only made my peace with them, but I’ve come to truly appreciate that there is an app for just about anything and everything.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 15:31:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-was-skeptical-but-now-im-glad-theres-an-app-for-everything/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[These Luxury Cars Don't Cost a Ton to Maintain ]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/luxury-cars-dont-cost-a-ton-to-maintain/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tyler Dupont]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/2025_lexus_ls_500_004.jpg" length="978" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Luxury Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sedans]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Upscale comfort, modest upkeep. Discover luxury cars that stay affordable to maintain.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Luxury cars often carry a reputation for breathtaking maintenance bills. Expensive parts, complex electronics, and specialized service can quickly turn ownership into a financial headache. Yet not every premium badge demands a blank check. A careful search reveals a handful of upscale models that combine comfort, performance, and technology with surprisingly manageable upkeep costs.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 15:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/luxury-cars-dont-cost-a-ton-to-maintain/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Ways Smaller Tech Is Better Tech]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-smaller-tech-is-better-tech/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/person-holding-the-samsung-galaxy-z-fold-7-showing-the-side-profile-54642279054-o.jpg" length="274" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple App Store]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Is it worth sacrificing battery life? For many of us—yes.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Companies continue to produce smaller and thinner tech, even though many of us are perfectly fine with the size of our current devices. Ultimately, though, we’re all better off due to this ongoing drive to make tech as small as possible.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 15:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ways-smaller-tech-is-better-tech/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Common Smartphone Mistakes You Should Avoid]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/smartphone-mistakes-to-avoid/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/a-samsung-galaxy-phone-with-an-alert-symbol-covered-in-water-droplets-on-the-screen.jpg" length="1045" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Maintenance & Optimization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Avoid smartphone regrets now!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Most of us hope our smartphones last for years, but without realizing it, we often make small mistakes that affect their performance and overall lifespan. From bad charging practices to skipping software updates and exposing your phone to extreme conditions, here are some common mistakes you must avoid.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sun, 21 Sep 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/smartphone-mistakes-to-avoid/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[9 iPadOS 26 Features That Made Me Upgrade Right Away]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ipados-26-features-that-made-me-upgrade-right-away/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Yash Wate]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/ipados-features-that-are-worth-upgrading-for.jpg" length="367" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPadOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPad]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
